## Example 3 — Use the Compound Interest Formula

Luciana deposits `$1700` into a savings account paying `1.8%` annual interest compounded monthly.

Find the balance after `5` years.

`A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)`

`= 1700(1 + 0.018/12)^(12*5)`

`≈ 1859.97`

So after `5` years, the balance is about:

`$1859.97`

